info.name: Assignment Node js
info.description:
**Description:**

- This API provides endpoints for user authentication and streaming content management.
    
- All endpoints that manage streaming content are protected by JWT-based authentication.
    
- Use the Auth folder to register or log in a user and obtain a JWT token, which should be sent in the `Authorization` header for streaming endpoints
    

**BaseUrls:**

- Local -> localhost:3000
    
- Production -> https://assignment-production-8f0e.up.railway.app

item.name: Auth

request.description: **Description :** Register a new user. Returns a JWT token on success.

response.name: 400 Bad request ( name exceeding characters )
429 Too Many Post requests
429 Too many Post requests

item.description:
Endpoints for user registration and login.

- **Register:** Create a new user by providing `name`, `email`, and `password`.
    
- **Login:** Authenticate an existing user using `email` and `password`.
    
- **Output:** Returns a JWT token that must be included in headers for all protected endpoints (`Bearer` ).
